Fama-French Monthly 5 Factor Returns

The following tables show the monthly returns of the five factors for different time periods. The full period spreads show that all five factors are effective (positive spreads) with momentum being the most effective with the highest spread.

Full Period - 1963-07-31 to 2019-10-31

Size Value Investment Profitability Momentum
0.79 1.06 0.95 0.91 1.85

By Decade

While all factors are positive overall, each factor is subject to long periods (a decade or more) of underperformance. In the most recent decade (2010 - 2019) all the factors have been weak with the exception of momentum, which has done very well.

Factor performance conditional on Yield Curve Slope

In the first four charts we look at the average returns to factors when the yield curve steepens or flattens by more than 5 bps. The 5 bps threshold is used for both daily and monthly data. This analysis ignores days (and months) where the yield curve changes by less than 5 bps.

Average Monthly Performance of all 5 Factors

Yield Curve 1963 - 2019-10-31 1963 - 1990 1990 - 2007 2007 - 2019-10-31
Steepens > 5 bps 1.04 1.639 0.618 2.29
Flattens > 5 bps 0.74 1.037 1.348 -0.386

Sources: The Fama-French factors can be downloaded from the Kenneth R. French Data Library. The slope of the yield curve is measured by the spread between the 10-year and 2-year Treasury yields, FRED data codes T10Y2YM and T10Y2Y.
